<topic id="switching-between-open-tabs">
  <title>Switching and Moving File Tabs</title><prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Switch file tabs</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Move file tabs</indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>There are two keyboard shortcuts that can be used for cycling through the opened file tabs:<dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_tab"/></dt>
          <dd>Switches between the tabs with opened files in the order most recent ones first.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_tab"/></dt>
          <dd>Switches between the tabs with opened files in the reverse order.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></p>
    <p>There are also two shortcuts for moving the current tab:<dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_alt_comma"/></dt>
          <dd>Moves the current file tab one position to the left.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_alt_period"/></dt>
          <dd>Moves the current file tab one position to the right.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></p>
  </body>
</topic>
